Username: EvanSTP

Set up account
git config --global user.name "EvanSTP"
git config --global user.email "evannm.hill@gmail.com"

Clone Repository
git clone https://github.com/EvanSTP/<repository-name>.git

Branching
git status 
List your current branch
git branch
Lists all branches
git branch <name>
List all files in current branch
git ls-files 
List all files in specific branch
git ls-tree -r <name> --name-only
Create a new branch with <name>
git push origin <name> 
Push the new branch to GitHub
git checkout <source-branch-name> -- <path/to/file>
Copy a file to the new branch

Deleting a Branch
git checkout main
Move off of to-be-deleted branch
git branch -d <name>
Safe deletion of <name>. Will not delete if unmerged changes. -D forces deletion. 
git push origin --delete <name>
Delete branch from GitHub.  

Update Local Respository
Navigate to the correct repository
cd /path/to/your/local/repo
Check you are on the correct branch (main vs master)
git checkout main
Pull the changes
git pull origin main
# or git pull

Send Changes Back
Stage the changes
git add . 
# or git add <specific-file>
Commit the changes
git commit -m "Description of your changes"
Push the changes
git push origin main

Remove a Commit
git rebase -i HEAD~2
Then in vim, change "pick" to "d" or "drop", save the file, then 
git push -f

Resolve a Merge Conflict
git status
List files under unmerged status
***Manually edit the conflicted files and look for the conflict markers (lines with <<<<<<< HEAD, =======, and >>>>>>>). Decide which version of the code to keep, then remove the markers.
git add <filename>
Stage the resolved file
git commit -m "Resolved merge conflicts and committed changes"
Finalize the merge locally. 
git pull
Pull again. 
